reviewText: I freaking love old Mexican movies! And these are excellent quality. But I was disappointed to find that there are no subtitles (none for Spanish or English or any other language). It would be easier to understand the dialogue if I could read subtitles, especially since Spanish isn't my first language and the sound quality is a little rough given how old the movie is.
Great old movies. Sometimes I like to go back and watch these movies. I was maybe 10 or 11 when color TV transmission started on my hometown.
I'm gonna get to the point quick if you like/love pinporo movies not all his movies are good but this one right here is pretty cool; It made me laugh me & my family had a blast.....
